<br>
A player loans his lvl 15 character to his brother.  The character is asked to do a trade of a 30k robe and the character then takes the robe and gives it away or sells it to twink out his characters.   The guild leader of the victim contacts the guild leader of the character who took the robe to see if the robe can be recovered.  The guild is small and doesnt have that much money or the forces to raid to get a replacement robe.  The GM's say all trades are final and that they cannot do a replacement under these circumstances.  Okay...here is the question?  Does the guild leader of the thief replace the robe?  <br>
<br>
Tell me what you think on this one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
